{"componentChunkName":"component---src-layouts-blog-post-layout-js","path":"/blog/how-to-upload-images-and-files-to-your-shopify-store","result":{"pageContext":{"id":451,"date":"2021-02-20T08:09:30","date_gmt":"2021-02-20T08:09:30","guid":{"rendered":"https://www.ezfy.club/?p=451"},"modified":"2021-02-20T08:14:27","modified_gmt":"2021-02-20T08:14:27","slug":"how-to-upload-images-and-files-to-your-shopify-store","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https://www.ezfy.club/how-to-upload-images-and-files-to-your-shopify-store/","title":{"rendered":"How to upload images and files to your Shopify store"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Shopify has an excellence system built in every store of file storage. In there you&#8217;re able to host your images, videos or files, and have an unique URL generated for each of them that you can use wherever you wish.<br><br>In this tutorial we&#8217;ll show you how you can host your files in less than 30 seconds.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Locating the file system in your admin page</h3>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>In your Shopify admin, navigate to <strong>Settings &gt; Files</strong>.<br><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1708\" height=\"793\" class=\"wp-image-453\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/navigate.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/navigate.jpg 1708w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/navigate-600x279.jpg 600w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/navigate-1200x557.jpg 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/navigate-768x357.jpg 768w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/navigate-1536x713.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1708px) 100vw, 1708px\" /></li><li>On the <strong>files</strong> page, click on the <strong>Upload Files</strong> button on the top right.</li><li>Upload the files you need and you&#8217;re ready to go! Now just copy the URL of the generated file and use it as per your wish.</li></ol>\n","protected":fa